In terms of functionality, the file exhibits behaviors typical of adware and PUA, such as possible bundling with other software without explicit user consent. While specific Features like URLs or IPs were not extracted, the presence of generic indicators like signature mismatch and timestamps indicate attempts at evasion. Key mitigations include utilizing robust antivirus programs to detect and block such files and educating users on discerning potentially unwanted software and downloading software from trusted sources. Users should also regularly update their systems and employ host-based intrusion detection systems (HIDS) to detect suspicious activities indicative of malicious behaviors.
